<task id="task_BA6EACA3039C40AEA5605E1D8C76E646"> 
  <title>Create a custom report</title> 
  <shortdesc>Steps that describe how to save a report's current configuration
	 as a new custom report for all users to see. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <prolog> 
	 <metadata> 
		<othermeta name="solution" content="Analytics"/> 
		<othermeta name="topic" content="Reports and analytics"/> </metadata>
  </prolog> 
  <taskbody> 
	 <context id="context_AF48FD4A460B4ADAAF0ED4267D89E4CB"> 
		<p>Only administrators can create a custom report. When you create a
		  custom report, it is added to the main reporting menu next to the report on
		  which it is based. 
		</p> 
		<p> 
		  <b>To create a custom report</b> 
		</p> 
	 </context> 
	 <steps id="steps_628D85CC4D664F7BA2DDC6C675EBA60B"> 
		<step id="step_0C0A69562248441888325DBCCBCC8EFC"> 
		  <cmd>Run a report and configure it as necessary. 
		  </cmd> 
		</step> 
		<step id="step_028D9F28D4B248F2886D855190948BBF"> 
		  <cmd>Click 
			 <uicontrol>More</uicontrol> &gt; 
			 <uicontrol>Create Custom Report</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd> 
		</step> 
		<step id="step_570715C14846480BB8C7657401397594"> 
		  <cmd>Name the report, then click 
			 <uicontrol>Save.</uicontrol> 
		  </cmd> 
		  <info>Ensure that you do not duplicate an existing report name. 
		  </info> 
		</step> 
	 </steps> 
  </taskbody> 
  <related-links> 
	 <link
	 href="http://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/reference/index.html?f=customize_menus"
	 scope="external" format="http"> 
		<linktext>Menu Customizing 
		</linktext> 
	 </link> 
  </related-links> 
</task> 
